The 3 jobs that will survive the AI revolution

According to Gates, three fields will survive (and thrive) in the AI era. W=
hy? Because AI isn=E2=80=99t ready to replace them just yet.=20

Here=E2=80=99s the breakdown:

1. Coders =E2=80=93 Because AI Can=E2=80=99t Code Itself (Yet)

Developers are still needed to refine, debug and push AI development forwar=
d.
AI is only as good as the humans training it.

Gates believes that as AI evolves, coders will be in higher demand to creat=
e and optimize these systems.

=E2=80=9CAI will need human coders to evolve. If you=E2=80=99re in tech, yo=
u=E2=80=99re not out of the game.=E2=80=9D

2. Energy Experts =E2=80=93 Too High-Stakes to Automate

Energy grids, nuclear plants, and renewable systems are too complex to hand=
 over to machines.

Gates believes human oversight is critical for safety and strategy.

AI can assist but the responsibility for keeping the lights on (literally) =
stays with humans.

 =E2=80=9CWould you trust AI to run a nuclear reactor? Didn=E2=80=99t think=
 so.=E2=80=9D

3. Biologists =E2=80=93 AI Can Analyze, But It Can=E2=80=99t Discover

AI can identify patterns in data, but it can=E2=80=99t replicate human intu=
ition and creativity.

Breakthroughs in biology from gene editing to disease cures require human i=
nnovation.

AI can support biologists, but it can=E2=80=99t replace the human mind behi=
nd major discoveries.

 =E2=80=9CAI can process data. But it takes a human to make the breakthroug=
h.=E2=80=9D

The Future of Work =3D Adapt or Get Left Behind

Gates isn=E2=80=99t sugarcoating this because AI will change everything. Ag=
ree??

